Class MachineLearningTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • MachineLearningTest

  • public class MachineLearningTest
extends java.lang.Object
    MachineLearningTest is class that is used to test the MachineLearning class of static methods. MachineLearningTest can show you the implementation and the calculations of MachineLearning

      • testCosineSimilarity

        public void testCosineSimilarity()
        Tests the cosineSimilarity method from MachineLearning(Tests are for each assertEquals call). Tests: test two positive vectors, test a vector with negative numbers to a vector with positive numbers, test two arrays that are of different length (returns 0), test two arrays with larger numbers, and test for a divide by zero error. MachineLearning.cosineSimilarity(float[], float[])
        See Also:
        Test, TestCase

      • testEuclideanDistance

        public void testEuclideanDistance()
        Tests the euclideanDistance method from MachineLearning(Tests are for each assertEquals call). Tests: test two positive vectors, test a vector with negative numbers to a vector with positive numbers, test two arrays that are of different length (returns 0), test two arrays with larger numbers, and test with a vector that has no distance. MachineLearning.euclideanDistance(float[], float[])
        See Also:
        Test, TestCase

      • testCosAndEucTogether

        public void testCosAndEucTogether()
        Tests the cosineSimilarity and euclideDistance methods from MachineLearning together to check that the methods do not change the arrays (vectors). MachineLearning.cosineSimilarity(float[], float[]), MachineLearning.euclideanDistance(float[], float[])
        See Also:
        Test, TestCase

      • testHammingDistance

        public void testHammingDistance()
        Tests the hammingDistance method from MachineLearning(Tests are for each assertEquals call). Tests: test a normal pair of codes, do another a test that is the same way, test two codes that are completely different, test two codes that are the exact same, and test two codes that are different lengths (returns 0) MachineLearning.hammingDistance(String, String)
        See Also:
        Test, TestCase
